These were SOOO GOOD! However, here are the adjustments I made, based on what I had in my cupboards and fridge: 

3 tablespoons of Italian seasoning because I didn't have any of the fresh herbs listed; 

regular mustard because I didn't have dry mustard; 

Panko breadcrumbs due to no Italian breadcrumbs; 

Cayenne Pepper because I didn't have anything labeled 'Red Pepper', although Google says they're the same, lol;

Grated parmesan cheese because I didn't have any shredded cheese.

Also, I'm not familiar with the 'melted butter' or whatever is listed. So I melted 3 tablespoons of salted butter in the microwave formed my meatballs on a cookie sheet that was lined with foil, and then drizzled the melted butter over them. 

Again, they were SOOO GOOOD! 

Sorry, forgot to take a pic, lol!
